io.nats.stan

Interface Subscription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public interface Subscription
extends AutoCloseable
    A client uses a Subscription object to receive messages that have been published to a subject.

    Each Subscription object is unique, even if the subscription is to the same subject. This means that if Connection.subscribe("foo", cb) is called twice in a row, each of the resulting Subscription objects will be unique, and any message delivered on subject "foo" will be delivered individually to both Subscription objects.
